{"_id":"3bnp6CrWiRHKsktr","name":"Mother Instructions.","permission":{"default":0,"vVRzTNcybBml63HZ":3},"folder":"","flags":{},"content":"<h1>Rolls</h1>\n<p>Rolls can be pushed by clicking on the Push icon in the chat window. The PC token needs to be selected.&nbsp; When a roll is pushed the PC's Stress level will automatically be increased by 1.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Right clicking on any Attributes, Skills or Equipment will display a dialogue box allowing dice to be added or subtracted from the roll.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>If you want to roll ad-hoc dice and dont want touse the macros (See below); you can roll Base dice by putting:</p>\n<p><strong>/r xdb </strong>for Base dice and <strong>/r xds</strong> for Stress dice, where x is the number of dice.&nbsp; For both just put&nbsp; <strong>/r 4db + 2ds</strong></p>\n<h1>Character &amp; Synth sheets</h1>\n<p>If the players are running a Synth and the rest of the party are aware that the PC is a Synth use the Synth sheet.&nbsp; If the other players are unaware use the normal character sheet and disregard Stress, Radiation, Conditions and Consumables. Though you may want the player to \"roll\" against these to maintain the pretext that they are human.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>NPC's</h2>\n<p>As the character sheets are the same for Characters and NPC's there are not seperate templates for these.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>On the Character and Synth sheets there is an NPC check box (only visible to the GM).&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>If this is checked, when the actor is dragged on to the Scene the Token will be set to <em>Unlinked</em> and <em>Hostile</em>.</p>\n<p><strong>Unchecking the NPC box will not affect existing tokens.</strong></p>\n<h1>General Tab</h1>\n<p style=\"margin: 0in; font-family: Signika; font-size: 10.5pt;\">Roll against attributes by clicking on the attribute name, not the number.&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0in; font-family: Signika; font-size: 10.5pt;\">For Stress tests click on Stress to roll (publicly) against the stress table.&nbsp; &nbsp;The result will appear in chat and any modifiers need to be applied manually.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0in; font-family: Signika; font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Experience, Radiation and Conditions.</h2>\n<p>Left click to set increment the counter and right click to decrement. These are just indicators and have no direct effect to rolls etc.</p>\n<p>\"Panicked\" condition will automatically set on panic rolls of 7+.&nbsp; This triggers the \"More Panic\" mechanics in the system.&nbsp; To remove the Panicked condition just right click on the dot.&nbsp; This will reset the PC's panic level to 0.&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Consumables</h2>\n<p>These fields are not automatically updated by items so the players will need to add the totals as required.&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Armor</h2>\n<p>The Armor value is updated based on the armor rating of items added to the players inventory.&nbsp; &nbsp; The player rolls armor checks by clicking on Armor.&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Skills/Talents Tab.</h1>\n<h2>Skills</h2>\n<p>Add skills values as required.&nbsp; Left click to roll against any particular skill.&nbsp; Controlling attribute dice are automatically added to the roll.&nbsp; Right clicking on the skill will pop a dialogue box to add/remove dice from the roll.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Clicking on the spanner icon&nbsp; will display the Stunts for that skill at the bottom of the sheet (this is a toggle switch).&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Talents</h2>\n<p>Talents, created under Items, can be dragged on to the&nbsp; character sheet.&nbsp; Any game mechanics arising from the talent need to be applied manually.&nbsp; Left clicking on the talent name will display the talent description at the bottom of the sheet (this is a toggle switch).&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Inventory Tab.</h1>\n<p>Drag and drop Weapons, Items and Armor as required.&nbsp; Encumbrance will increase based on the items weight.&nbsp; This is displayed as&nbsp; Current/Max.&nbsp; The two arrows indicate the limit (Str *2).&nbsp; When over this the indicator will flash.&nbsp; Encumbrance penalties need to be applied manually for any rolls.&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Creature Sheets</h1>\n<p>Creature checks are all performed as private GM rolls.&nbsp; &nbsp;The system also supports attack tables.&nbsp; To use this create the attack table as normal in the Alien Creature Tables folder. The table will then appears as a selectable option in the Attack Table drop down.&nbsp; To roll against the table hit the \"Roll Attack\" button.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Vehicle Sheets</h1>\n<p>Heavy weapons (Items) can be dragged on the Inventory and behave the same as weapons on the character sheets.&nbsp; But they do not take into account any modifiers from the PC firing the weapon so use right mouse click to add any modifiers.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Territory sheets</h1>\n<p>General tab provides two text boxes to give a general description and specific data about the sectors.&nbsp; &nbsp;The systems tab allows individual systems (created as Items) to be dragged on to the sheet.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Items</h1>\n<p style=\"margin: 0in; font-family: Signika; font-size: 10.5pt;\">Specific sheets are available for Armor, Systems/Planets, Talents and Weapons.&nbsp; For general items use \"Item\" and the drop down to select the type.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0in; font-family: Signika; font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Skill-Stunts</h2>\n<p>The system will create&nbsp; a&nbsp; folder in Items called Skill-Stunts and automatically populate with each of the skills.&nbsp; Just open the skill and using the editor add the required text from the rules and format as required.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0in; font-family: Signika; font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<h1>Macros</h1>\n<p style=\"margin: 0in; font-family: Signika; font-size: 10.5pt;\">The Alien Compendium has 2 macros to allow ad-hoc rolls against Mother and Creature tables.&nbsp; The tables need to be in the correct folder for the macros to display them in the drop down.&nbsp; &nbsp;These are private GM rolls.&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0in; font-family: Signika; font-size: 10.5pt;\">There are also 2 macros for ad hoc dice rolls.&nbsp; The GM macro is a private GM roll.&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0in; font-family: Signika; font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<h2 style=\"margin: 0in; font-family: Signika; font-size: 10.5pt;\"><strong>Multiple Initiative Rolls for&nbsp;<span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"font-family: Signika, sans-serif;\">XENOMORPHS.</span></strong></h2>\n<p style=\"margin: 0in; font-family: Signika; font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"font-family: Signika, sans-serif;\">Some creatures have multiple attacks based on their speed.&nbsp; Unfortunatly (currently) in Foundry VTT there is not way to emulate this mechanic but shteff#8724 on Discord has developed the following:&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0in; font-family: Signika; font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0in; font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11.0pt;\"><strong>IMPORTANT: you must have \"The Furnace\" module with the 'Advanced Macros' option ON. </strong></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0in; font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11.0pt;\">So, once you have added your aliens to the combat tracker, just select token you want to add again and click on the macro. The <span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\">Macro should be set to 'script'.</span></p>\n<table border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p style=\"margin: 0in; font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt;\"><code>if(!token) return;</code></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0in; font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt;\"><code>if(!game.combat) return;</code></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0in; font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt;\"><code>game.combat.createCombatant({tokenId: token.id, hidden: token.hidden});</code></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p style=\"margin: 0in; font-family: Signika; font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0in; font-family: Signika; font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Signika;\">Alternatively the <strong>Reverse Initiative</strong> module no only reverses the Initiative but allows you to duplicate an actor in the Combat tracker before you make the initiative rolls.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0in; font-family: Signika; font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<h1 style=\"margin: 0in; font-family: Signika; font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18pt;\">Dice So Nice</span></h1>\n<p style=\"margin: 0in; font-family: Signika; font-size: 10.5pt;\">Alien RPG is fully compatible with Dice So Nice.&nbsp; In the DsN configuration you (or your players) will find two sets of Alien dice, one without numbers and one with.&nbsp; By default the dice without numbers is selected.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0in; font-family: Signika; font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0in; font-family: Signika; font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</p>"}
{"_id":"8C9IkPq2b9xsxICq","name":"Anweisungen f√ºr MUTTER.","permission":{"default":0,"PqqJOOTYGlJLLzJT":3},"folder":"","flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.i2zFNSZpCMfaC95j"}},"content":"<div style=\"mso-element: para-border-div; border: none; border-bottom: solid #782E22 1.5pt; padding: 0cm 0cm 0cm 0cm;\">\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-outline-level: 1; border: none; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #782E22 1.5pt; padding: 0cm; mso-padding-alt: 0cm 0cm 0cm 0cm;\"><span lang=\"DE\" style=\"font-size: 24.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-font-kerning: 18.0pt; mso-ansi-language: DE; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;\">Proben</span></p>\n</div>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 6.0pt 0cm 6.0pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"DE\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: DE; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;\">Proben k&ouml;nnen strapaziert werden, indem man die &ldquo;Push&rdquo;-Fl&auml;che im Chat Fenster klickt. Die Figur muss dazu angew&auml;hlt werden. Wenn eine Probe strapaziert wird, steigert sich der Stress der Figur automatisch um einen Schritt. </span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 6.0pt 0cm 6.0pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"DE\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: DE; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;\">Ein Rechtsklick auf Attribute, Fertigkeiten oder Ausr&uuml;stung zeigt einen Dialog an, in dem Bonusw&uuml;rfel hinzugef&uuml;gt oder abgezogen werden kann. </span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 6.0pt 0cm 6.0pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"DE\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: DE; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;\">Wenn ad-hoc W&uuml;rfe ben&ouml;tigt werden und man die Makros (s.u.) nicht benutzen will, dann geht das auch &uuml;ber den Chat:&nbsp; </span><strong><span lang=\"DE\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: DE; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;\">/r xdb&nbsp;</span></strong><span lang=\"DE\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: DE; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;\">f&uuml;r Basisw&uuml;rfel und&nbsp;<strong>/r xds</strong>&nbsp;f&uuml;r Stressw&uuml;rfel, wobei x f&uuml;r die Anzahl der W&uuml;rfel steht.&nbsp;Wenn beide W&uuml;rfelsorten ben&ouml;tigt werden, kann man bspw. &nbsp;<strong>/r 4db + 2ds </strong>eingeben.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 6.0pt 0cm 6.0pt 0cm;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<div style=\"mso-element: para-border-div; border: none; border-bottom: solid #782E22 1.5pt; padding: 0cm 0cm 0cm 0cm;\">\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-outline-level: 1; border: none; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #782E22 1.5pt; padding: 0cm; mso-padding-alt: 0cm 0cm 0cm 0cm;\"><span lang=\"DE\" style=\"font-size: 24.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-font-kerning: 18.0pt; mso-ansi-language: DE; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;\">Charakter- &amp; Synthb&ouml;gen</span></p>\n</div>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 6.0pt 0cm 6.0pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"DE\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: DE; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;\">Wenn Spieler einen Synth spielen und dem Rest der Gruppe dies bekannt ist, benutze den Synth-Charakterbogen. Wenn die anderen Spieler von der wahren Natur des Synth nichts wissen, benutze einen normalen Charakterbogen. In diesem Fall ignoriere Stress, Strahlung, Zust&auml;nde und Verbrauchsg&uuml;ter. Es kann sinnvoll sein, den Spieler trotzdem w&uuml;rfeln zu lassen, um die Illusion aufrechtzuerhalten.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 6.0pt 0cm 6.0pt 0cm;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>NSC's</h2>\n<p><span lang=\"DE\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: DE; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;\">Wenn Spieler einen Synth spielen und der Rest der Gruppe dies bekannt ist, benutze den Synth-Charakterbogen. Wenn die anderen Spieler von der wahren Natur des Synth nichts wissen, benutze einen normalen Charakterbogen. In diesem Fall ignoriere Stress, Strahlung, Zust&auml;nde und Verbrauchsg&uuml;ter. </span></p>\n<p><span lang=\"DE\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: DE; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;\"><strong>Es kann sinnvoll sein, den Spieler trotzdem w&uuml;rfeln zu lassen, um die Illusion aufrechtzuerhalten.</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div style=\"mso-element: para-border-div; border: none; border-bottom: solid #782E22 1.5pt; padding: 0cm 0cm 0cm 0cm;\">\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-outline-level: 1; border: none; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #782E22 1.5pt; padding: 0cm; mso-padding-alt: 0cm 0cm 0cm 0cm;\"><strong><span lang=\"DE\" style=\"font-size: 24.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-font-kerning: 18.0pt; mso-ansi-language: DE; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;\">Allgemeine Registerkarte</span></strong></p>\n</div>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: normal;\"><span lang=\"DE\" style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: 'Signika',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: DE; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;\">W&uuml;rfle Proben gegen Attribute durch Klicken auf den Attributnamen, nicht auf den Wert.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: normal;\"><span lang=\"DE\" style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: 'Signika',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: DE; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: Signika, serif; font-size: 10.5pt;\">F&uuml;r Stressproben klicke auf Stress f&uuml;r einen &ouml;ffentlichen Wurf auf der Stresstabelle. Das Resultat wird im Chat-Protokoll angezeigt und etwaige Modifikatoren m&uuml;ssen manuell angewendet werden.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0in; font-family: Signika; font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<div style=\"mso-element: para-border-div; border: none; border-bottom: solid #782E22 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #782E22 .75pt; padding: 0cm 0cm 0cm 0cm;\">\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-outline-level: 2; border: none; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #782E22 .75pt; padding: 0cm; mso-padding-alt: 0cm 0cm 0cm 0cm;\"><span lang=\"DE\" style=\"font-size: 18.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: DE; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;\">Erfahrung, Strahlung und Zust&auml;nde</span></p>\n</div>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 6.0pt 0cm 6.0pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"DE\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: DE; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;\">Ein Linksklick steigert den Wert, ein Rechtsklick senkt ihn. Diese Werte sind nur zur Anzeige und haben keine Auswirkung auf andere Proben. </span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 6.0pt 0cm 6.0pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"DE\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: DE; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;\">Der \"Panik&ldquo;-Zustand wird automatisch aktiviert, sobald eine Panikprobe 7 oder mehr ergibt. Das l&ouml;st die &bdquo;Mehr Panik&ldquo;-Mechanik im System aus. Um den Zustand zu entfernen, reicht ein Rechtsklick auf den Knopf. Dies setzt den Panikwert zur&uuml;ck auf 0.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 6.0pt 0cm 6.0pt 0cm;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<div style=\"mso-element: para-border-div; border: none; border-bottom: solid #782E22 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #782E22 .75pt; padding: 0cm 0cm 0cm 0cm;\">\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-outline-level: 2; border: none; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #782E22 .75pt; padding: 0cm; mso-padding-alt: 0cm 0cm 0cm 0cm;\"><span lang=\"DE\" style=\"font-size: 18.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: DE; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;\">Verbrauchsg&uuml;ter</span></p>\n</div>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 6.0pt 0cm 6.0pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"DE\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: DE; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;\">Diese Felder werden nicht automatisch durch Gegenst&auml;nde angepasst und dies muss manuell erfolgen.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 6.0pt 0cm 6.0pt 0cm;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<div style=\"mso-element: para-border-div; border: none; border-bottom: solid #782E22 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #782E22 .75pt; padding: 0cm 0cm 0cm 0cm;\">\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-outline-level: 2; border: none; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #782E22 .75pt; padding: 0cm; mso-padding-alt: 0cm 0cm 0cm 0cm;\"><span lang=\"DE\" style=\"font-size: 18.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: DE; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;\">Panzerung</span></p>\n</div>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif; font-size: 12pt;\">Die Panzerung wird durch entsprechende Gegenst&auml;nde im Inventar angepasst. Um eine Panzerungsprobe zu w&uuml;rfeln, klickt der Spieler auf die </span><em style=\"font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif; font-size: 12pt;\">Panzerung</em><span style=\"font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif; font-size: 12pt;\"> -&Uuml;berschrift.</span>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h1><strong><span style=\"font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif; font-size: 24pt;\">Fertigkeiten Registerkarte</span>.</strong></h1>\n<div style=\"mso-element: para-border-div; border: none; border-bottom: solid #782E22 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #782E22 .75pt; padding: 0cm 0cm 0cm 0cm;\">\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-outline-level: 2; border: none; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #782E22 .75pt; padding: 0cm; mso-padding-alt: 0cm 0cm 0cm 0cm;\"><span lang=\"DE\" style=\"font-size: 18.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: DE; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;\">Fertigkeiten</span></p>\n</div>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 6.0pt 0cm 6.0pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"DE\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: DE; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;\">Trage die ben&ouml;tigten Werte direkt ein.&nbsp;Ein Linksklick w&uuml;rfelt gegen die entsprechende Fertigkeit.&nbsp;Die relevanten Attributwerte werden automatisch verrechnet. Ein Rechtsklick &ouml;ffnete einen Dialog, in dem die Anzahl der W&uuml;rfel angepasst werden kann. </span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 6.0pt 0cm 6.0pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"DE\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: DE; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;\">Ein Klick auf den Schraubenschl&uuml;ssel zeigt die m&ouml;glichen Stunts f&uuml;r die Fertigkeit an (das ist ein Umschalter).&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 6.0pt 0cm 6.0pt 0cm;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<h2 class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 6.0pt 0cm 6.0pt 0cm;\"><span style=\"font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif; font-size: 18pt;\">Talente</span></h2>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 6.0pt 0cm 6.0pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"DE\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: DE; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;\">Talente, die im Gegenstandsverzeichnis eingepflegt sind, k&ouml;nnen auf den Charakterbogen gezogen werden. Etwaige Spielmechaniken, die aus den Talenten resultieren, m&uuml;ssen manuell angepasst werden. Ein Linksklick auf das Talent zeigt die Beschreibung unten auf dem Blatt an (Umschalter).&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div style=\"mso-element: para-border-div; border: none; border-bottom: solid #782E22 1.5pt; padding: 0cm 0cm 0cm 0cm;\">\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-outline-level: 1; border: none; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #782E22 1.5pt; padding: 0cm; mso-padding-alt: 0cm 0cm 0cm 0cm;\"><strong><span lang=\"DE\" style=\"font-size: 24.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-font-kerning: 18.0pt; mso-ansi-language: DE; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;\">Inventar Registerkarte</span></strong></p>\n</div>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 6.0pt 0cm 6.0pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"DE\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: DE; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;\">Waffen k&ouml;nnen auf den Charakterbogen gezogen werden. Die Traglast wird entsprechend dem Gewicht des Gegenstandes angepasst. Dies wird als aktuell/max angezeigt. Die beiden Pfeile zeigen die Belastbarkeit (St *2) an. Wenn die Traglast &uuml;ber diesem Wert liegt, blinkt die Anzeige. Belastungsmodifikatoren m&uuml;ssen manuell angepasst werden.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 6.0pt 0cm 6.0pt 0cm;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<div style=\"mso-element: para-border-div; border: none; border-bottom: solid #782E22 1.5pt; padding: 0cm 0cm 0cm 0cm;\">\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-outline-level: 1; border: none; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #782E22 1.5pt; padding: 0cm; mso-padding-alt: 0cm 0cm 0cm 0cm;\"><strong><span lang=\"DE\" style=\"font-size: 24.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-font-kerning: 18.0pt; mso-ansi-language: DE; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;\">Kreaturen-Bogen</span></strong></p>\n</div>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 6.0pt 0cm 6.0pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"DE\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: DE; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;\">Proben f&uuml;r Kreaturen werden als private Spielleiterw&uuml;rfe gemacht. Das System unterst&uuml;tzt Angriffstabellen. Um diese zu nutzen, lege die Angriffe wie &uuml;blich in dem Alien Angriffe-Ordner an. Die Tabelle steht dann als Auswahlm&ouml;glichkeit in dem Drop-Down <u>Angriffstabelle</u> erscheinen. Um auf der Tabelle zu w&uuml;rfeln, klicke den &bdquo;Roll Attack&ldquo; Knopf.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 6.0pt 0cm 6.0pt 0cm;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<div style=\"mso-element: para-border-div; border: none; border-bottom: solid #782E22 1.5pt; padding: 0cm 0cm 0cm 0cm;\">\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-outline-level: 1; border: none; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #782E22 1.5pt; padding: 0cm; mso-padding-alt: 0cm 0cm 0cm 0cm;\"><strong><span lang=\"DE\" style=\"font-size: 24.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-font-kerning: 18.0pt; mso-ansi-language: DE; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;\">Fahrzeug-Bogen</span></strong></p>\n</div>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 6.0pt 0cm 6.0pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"DE\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: DE; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;\">Schwere Waffen (Gegenst&auml;nde) k&ouml;nnen auf den Bogen gezogen werden und werden genauso genutzt wie Waffen auf den Charakter-B&ouml;gen. Modifikatoren von den sie bedienenden SCs werden aber nicht automatisch angerechnet, also verwende einen Rechtsklick, um diese Modifikatoren einzugeben.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 6.0pt 0cm 6.0pt 0cm;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<div style=\"mso-element: para-border-div; border: none; border-bottom: solid #782E22 1.5pt; padding: 0cm 0cm 0cm 0cm;\">\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-outline-level: 1; border: none; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #782E22 1.5pt; padding: 0cm; mso-padding-alt: 0cm 0cm 0cm 0cm;\"><strong><span lang=\"DE\" style=\"font-size: 24.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-font-kerning: 18.0pt; mso-ansi-language: DE; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;\">Territorien-Bogen</span></strong></p>\n</div>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 6.0pt 0cm 6.0pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"DE\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: DE; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;\">Der <em>territory-</em>Bogen (im Charakterverzeichnis) bietet zwei Registerkarten f&uuml;r allgemeine Beschreibung und spezifische Sektor-Informationen.</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 6.0pt 0cm 6.0pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"DE\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: DE; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;\">Unter Systeme k&ouml;nnen individuell angelegte System (als Gegenst&auml;nde) auf den Bogen gezogen werden.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 6.0pt 0cm 6.0pt 0cm;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<div style=\"mso-element: para-border-div; border: none; border-bottom: solid #782E22 1.5pt; padding: 0cm 0cm 0cm 0cm;\">\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-outline-level: 1; border: none; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #782E22 1.5pt; padding: 0cm; mso-padding-alt: 0cm 0cm 0cm 0cm;\"><span lang=\"DE\" style=\"font-size: 24.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-font-kerning: 18.0pt; mso-ansi-language: DE; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;\"><strong>Gegenst&auml;nde</strong></span></p>\n</div>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: normal;\"><span lang=\"DE\" style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: 'Signika',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: DE; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;\">Eingabemasken f&uuml;r Panzerung, Systeme/Planeten, Talente und Waffen sind verf&uuml;gbar. F&uuml;r allgemeine Gegenst&auml;nde, w&auml;hle <em>item</em> aus der Auswahlliste.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0in; font-family: Signika; font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<div style=\"mso-element: para-border-div; border: none; border-bottom: solid #782E22 1.0pt; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #782E22 .75pt; padding: 0cm 0cm 0cm 0cm;\">\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-outline-level: 2; border: none; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #782E22 .75pt; padding: 0cm; mso-padding-alt: 0cm 0cm 0cm 0cm;\"><span lang=\"DE\" style=\"font-size: 18.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: DE; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;\">Fertigkeits-Stunts</span></p>\n</div>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 6.0pt 0cm 6.0pt 0cm;\"><span lang=\"DE\" style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: DE; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;\">Das System legt einen Ordner f&uuml;r Fertigkeitsstunts an und diesen automatisch mit den Fertigkeiten bev&ouml;lkern. &Ouml;ffne diese Eintr&auml;ge und f&uuml;ge den n&ouml;tigen Text aus den Regeln mit dem editor ein.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0in; font-family: Signika; font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<div style=\"mso-element: para-border-div; border: none; border-bottom: solid #782E22 1.5pt; padding: 0cm 0cm 0cm 0cm;\">\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; line-height: normal; mso-outline-level: 1; border: none; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #782E22 1.5pt; padding: 0cm; mso-padding-alt: 0cm 0cm 0cm 0cm;\"><span lang=\"DE\" style=\"font-size: 24.0pt; font-family: 'Times New Roman',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-font-kerning: 18.0pt; mso-ansi-language: DE; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;\"><strong>Makros</strong></span></p>\n</div>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: normal;\"><span lang=\"DE\" style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: 'Signika',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: DE; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;\">Das Alien Kompendium hat 2 Makros, die W&uuml;rfe auf der Mother- und Kreaturentabelle erlauben. Diese Tabelle m&uuml;ssen sich im richtigen Ordner befinden, damit die Makros sie in den Auswahllisten anzeigen. Die W&uuml;rfe sind private SL-W&uuml;rfe. </span></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: normal;\"><span lang=\"DE\" style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: 'Signika',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: DE; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: Signika, serif; font-size: 10.5pt;\">Zwei weitere Makros erm&ouml;glichen spontane &bdquo;ad-hoc&ldquo; W&uuml;rfe, wobei das GM Makro einen privaten SL-Wurf erzeugt.&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0in; font-family: Signika; font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<h2 style=\"margin: 0in; font-family: Signika; font-size: 10.5pt;\"><strong style=\"font-family: Signika, sans-serif;\"><span lang=\"DE\" style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; line-height: 107%; font-family: 'Signika',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: DE; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA;\">Merhfache Initiativew&uuml;rfe f&uuml;r</span></strong><strong>&nbsp;<span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"font-family: Signika, sans-serif;\">XENOMORPHS.</span></strong></h2>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: normal;\"><span lang=\"DE\" style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: 'Signika',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: DE; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;\">Einige Kreaturen haben aufgrund ihrer Geschwindigkeit mehrere Angriffe pro Runde. Leider bildet Foundry VTT dies (noch) nicht ab, aber shteff#8724 auf Discord hat diesen Ansatz entwickelt:</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0in; font-family: Signika; font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: normal;\"><strong>WICHTIG: \"The Furnace\"-Modul muss installiert und 'Advanced Macros' als ON gew&auml;hlt sein.</strong></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: normal;\"><span lang=\"DE\">Wenn die Kreatur dann im &ldquo;Begegnungs&rdquo;-tracker ist, w&auml;hle die Figur an und klicke das Makro an. </span>Das Makro sollte als <em>script</em> angelegt warden..</p>\n<table border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p style=\"margin: 0in; font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt;\"><code>if(!token) return;</code></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0in; font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt;\"><code>if(!game.combat) return;</code></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0in; font-family: Calibri; font-size: 11pt;\"><code>game.combat.createCombatant({tokenId: token.id, hidden: token.hidden});</code></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p style=\"margin: 0in; font-family: Signika; font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0in; font-family: Signika; font-size: 10.5pt;\"><span style=\"font-family: Signika;\">Alternativ kann man das Reverse Initiative Modul verwenden. Es kehrt nicht nur die Initiativereihenfolge um, sondern kann eine Figur im Combat Tracker (Begegnungen) auch duplizieren bevor die Initiative gew&uuml;rfelt wird.</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0in; font-family: Signika; font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<h1><strong><span style=\"font-size: 18pt;\">Dice So Nice</span></strong></h1>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: normal;\"><span lang=\"DE\" style=\"font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: 'Signika',serif; mso-fareast-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-bidi-font-family: 'Times New Roman'; mso-ansi-language: DE; mso-fareast-language: EN-GB;\">Alien RPG ist vollst&auml;ndig mit Dice So Nice kompatibel.&nbsp; In den DsN-Einstellungen findest du (oder deine Spieler) zwei Alien-W&uuml;rfels&auml;tze, einen mit Ziffern und einen ohne. Als Grundeinstellung sind die W&uuml;rfel ohne Ziffern ausgew&auml;hlt.</span></p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0in; font-family: Signika; font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</p>\n<p style=\"margin: 0in; font-family: Signika; font-size: 10.5pt;\">&nbsp;</p>"}
{"name":"MO/TH/ER Instructions.","permission":{"default":0,"QKKAD0kWDfGCQDcy":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"JournalEntry.u522l4MmxvdH1ZTt"}},"content":"<div class=\"alienrpg a.entity-link\">\n<p>This is a guide to using the core Alien RPG system. <br />Alien RPG is an UNOFFICIAL system for playing Alien RPG on Foundry VTT. <br /><br />This system only provides support for character, creature, items, system, talent and character sheets. <br />There is no game content or images in this system. <br />Should you wish to populate the system with game content for your own use please purchase the rules from Free League Publishing: https://frialigan.se/en/games/alien/ <br />My intention is to enable people to play Alien RPG remotely and not to create a fully enabled/automated system. Mother will still need to do some work. <br />Please do not ask me to provide content. <strong> Buy the system from Free League !</strong></p>\n<h1 class=\"headng\">Actors</h1>\nThere are three main types of Actors available in the system:\n<ul>\n<li>Characters</li>\n<li>Synthetics</li>\n<li>Creatures</li>\n</ul>\nIn this section I will go over the common areas of the Character and Synthetic sheets. <br /><br />\n<h2 class=\"headng\">Characters and Synthetics</h2>\n<h2 class=\"headng2\">General Tab</h2>\nIf a player is using a \"Secret Android\" they should use the Character sheet and roleplay as a normal PC just ignoring any Stress (just reset it to 0 if they get any), Radiation or Condition effects. <br />This will enable them to keep up the pretence that they are a normal PC until the big reveal. At which point they can increase their stats in line with the rules for Synthetics. Otherwise, they should use the Synthetic sheet which dispenses with any stats, conditions etc that do not effect them. <br /><br />The header sections for the Character and Synthetic sheets are very similar with the exception that the Synthetic sheet does not have Stress. <br />&nbsp;<span class=\"character-header\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"synthetic-header\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; <br />For Strength, Agility, Wits and Empathy rolls a Left mouse click will roll the value and Right mouse click will display a modifier box allowing additional dice to be added or subtracted as indicated by the GM. <br />&nbsp;<span class=\"agil-mod\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; <br /><br />In the system health is not automatically calculated so needs to be updated manually as per the rules. <br /><br />Stress is automatically added on a push (see Rolls below) but any other adjustments to a characters Stress need to be made manually. <br /><br />The Stress value is taken into account on all dice rolls. <br />For Panic rolls the player Left clicks on \"Stress\" and the result is displayed in the chat window. Right Clicking on \"Stress\" will display a modifier box to add or remove stress to the roll. <br />This will add/subtract the entered value (+x or -x) to the roll not effecting the number of dice. <br />&nbsp;<span class=\"stress-mod\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; <br />For the GM only an NPC box is visible. If this is checked when the actor is dragged on to the Scene the Token will be set to Unlinked and Hostile. Unchecking the NPC box will not affect existing tokens. <br />In the Career dropdown you can select the appropriate career for the PC.<br />The details boxes are text fields to record short details about the PC's. <br /><br />As per the rules the Synthetics do not have Signature Items. <br />&nbsp;<span class=\"character-details\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; <br />The left sidebar tracks Experience, Radiation, Conditions, Consumables and Armor. <br /><br />&nbsp;<span class=\"character-consumables\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"synthetic-consumables\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; <br /><br />Experience, Radiation and Conditions are check boxes, Left mouse click to set and Right mouse click to unset. <br />The \"Panicked\" condition will automatically set following panic rolls of 7+. This triggers the \"More Panic\" mechanics in the system. <br />To remove the Panicked condition just right click on the dot. <br />This will reset the PC's panic level to 0.<br />As they are not used Synthetics do not have Radiation or Condition check boxes. <br /><br /><strong>NOTE:</strong> This does not effect their Stress level. <br /><br />The consumables and Armor values are updated automatically based on the \"Active\" items in the PC's Inventory (See Inventory for more details.)<br />Supply rolls are made by clicking on the parachute icon.<br />Any failures (6's) will automatically be deducted from the total and the items giving that value will be decremented.<br /><br />In the system all the items \"Active\" consumable values are combined to give these totals. While not strictly as per the rules it is the most effective way to manage these assets so some manual intervention may be required by the player/GM. <br />For Armor rolls the player just clicks on \"Armor\" and the appropriate number of dice are rolled with the result appearing in the character window. <br /><br />\n<h2 class=\"headng2\">Stats Tab</h2>\n<p>The Stats tab lists the skills available to players. These are updated by the player during character creation. <br />&nbsp;<span class=\"moskills\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; <br />Left mouse click will roll the value and Right mouse click will display a modifier dialogue box and add/subtract base and/or stress dice for Characters and just base dice for Synthetics. Skill rolls are combined with the associated attribute values when making rolls. <br />Clicking on the spanner icon&nbsp;<span class=\"spanner-icon\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;next to a skill will display the appropriate stunts for that skill at the bottom of the sheet, a second click hides the description. (See Skill Stunts below). <br />&nbsp;<span class=\"talent-agenda\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; The Talents and Agenda/Story Cards sections allow the player/GM to drop talent and agenda items (See below) onto the characters sheet. Clicking on the name will display the items description at the bottom of the sheet. A second click hides the description. Right Clicking on the edit icon to the right will display a context menu allowing the PCs version of the item to be edited or deleted. <br />&nbsp;<span class=\"con-edit\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2 class=\"headng2\">Inventory Tab</h2>\n<p>At the top of the tab is the Encumbrance meter. This shows the \"Total Carried / Maximum Encumbrance\" where Maximum Encumbrance is Str *4. The two arrows on the Encumbrance show the point at which the PC should be taking penalties for being over encumbered. <br />&nbsp;<span class=\"enc\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; When the carried items exceed this point the bar will turn red and flash. <br />&nbsp;<span class=\"enc-warn\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; <br /><br />Items are dragged on to the sheet from item folders or Compendiums. By default, they will appear on the sheet as Inactive. Inactive items can be considered as being in a backpack/pocket/slung and do not contribute to Consumables, but they do contribute to Encumbrance. For gear owned but stored elsewhere (locker/room etc.) use the \"Ad Hoc\" text area at the bottom of the sheet the Quick-Insert module can be used to create a link (see Recommended Add-on Modules). Weapons cannot be fired when Inactive. <br />&nbsp;<span class=\"inv-inact\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; <br />Left clicking on the items image (1) will Activate the item. When Active right clicking on the item image will make it Inactive. Only Active weapons can be clicked on for rolls. <br /><br />Items can be edited or deleted by right clicking on the edit icon (2) which will display a context menu with edit/delete options. <br /><br />Some items have inline edit boxes (3) which enable you to edit some quantities (Rounds, Food, Water, Air) without the need to open the item. <br /><strong>NOTE: </strong>Items can be dropped on to the macro bar, though only Weapons will roll, so when using inline edit click on the number in the box, delete or backspace then enter the new number. Trying to highlight the number to edit will drag the entire item. <br /><br /></p>\n<h2 class=\"headng\">Creature Sheets</h2>\n<p>When a Creature dragged on to a Scene the Token will be set to Unlinked and Hostile. <br /><br />&nbsp;<span class=\"creature-header\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; <br />By default so values are entered for Mobility, Observation and Acid Splash as not all creatures have these stats. <br /><br />For Mobility, Armor, Armor Vs Fire, Observation and Acid Splash rolls, a Left mouse click will roll the value and Right mouse click (on all but Acid Splash) will display a modifier box allowing additional dice to be added or subtracted as indicated by the GM. As some creatures have a different armor stat against fire damage this is shown as a separate field. Where creatures have the \"Acid Splash\" ability the damage to be inflicted can entered in to the field. <br /><br />When the roll is made a pop up will appear requesting the damage inflicted on the creature by the PC. <br />&nbsp;<span class=\"acid-splash-popup\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; <br />The result of the combined dice will be displayed in the chat window. <br />Clicking on the Attack Table drop down will show a list of any attack tables that you have created in the \"Alien Tables&gt; Alien Creature Tables\" folder. Once selected the table can be rolled against by clicking on the \"Roll Attack\" button. <br />&nbsp;<span class=\"creature-attack-dropdown\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; <br />The result appears in the chat window as a GM only message so the GM can narrate the action and add more flair and detail if required. <br />As with all chat messages the result of any damage rolls can be seen by clicking on the dice icon in the chat window. <br />&nbsp;<span class=\"chat-roll\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; <br />The Special Abilities section allows quick notes to be added with respect to the Creature or situation. More detailed notes can be added on the Notes tab in the rich text editor.</p>\n<br /><br />\n<h2 class=\"headng\">Territories</h2>\n<p>The territories sheet allows you to create details about each of the sectors in space which you can share with the players. <br />&nbsp;<span class=\"territories-general\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; <br />On the Systems tab you can drag systems (created as Items), clicking on the system name will open the associated sheet. <br />The context menu can be used to edit and delete the system attached to that sector. <br />&nbsp;<span class=\"territories-systems\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;</p>\n<br /><br />\n<h2 class=\"headng\">Vehicles</h2>\n<p>Though not used very much within the game the Vehicles template allows you to create vehicles within the system. <br />These actors are designed as templates to allow vehicles to be incorporated into your games. As many of the stats are not rollable on the sheet. They should be used as modifiers for the PC making the test. <br />&nbsp;<span class=\"vehicle-general\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; <br /><br />The Inventory tab allows the PCs to roll for the weapons on that vehicle. The GM should make all the players \"Owners\" of the vehicle in order for them to interact with it. They should right click to activate the modifier box and add the appropriate number of attribute, skill and stress dice for the test. <br />&nbsp;<span class=\"vehicle-inv\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; <br />The Crew tab allows the GM/Players to record the Pilot and Gunner for the ship and the total of their attribute, skill and stress dice for reference. <br />&nbsp;<span class=\"vehicle-crew\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;</p>\n<br /><br />\n<h1 class=\"headng\">Items/Item Types</h1>\n<p>There are a number of Item types that can be created for use within the system:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Item - General equipment</li>\n<li>Weapon - Personal and Vehicle weapons</li>\n<li>Armor - Personal armor</li>\n<li>Talent - Talents for use within the system</li>\n<li>Planet-System - Details of planetary systems</li>\n<li>Skill-Stunt - Place holders that drive the Skill-Stunts pop up on character sheets</li>\n<li>Agenda - PC Agenda and Story cards</li>\n</ul>\n<br /><br />\n<h2 class=\"headng2\">Item</h2>\n<p>The item sheet is for generic items for use within the game. When a new item is created the type dropdown will dynamically change the sheet to include ant relevant stats for that item type on the Attributes tab. <br />&nbsp;<span class=\"item-dropdown\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; <br />Any stats entered for the item will have an in-system effect once the item is \"Active\". <br />The Consumables type is a general item that includes stats for Power, Food, Water and Air Supply for any homebrew items. <br /><br />The modifiers tab allows you to add any +/- effects using the item may have on the PCs attributes or skills. <br />&nbsp;<span class=\"modifiers-img\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; <br />Modifiers also have an in-system effect once the item is \"Active\".</p>\n<br /><br />\n<h2 class=\"headng2\">Weapon</h2>\n<p>Select the type on the sheet (Ranged or Melee) and the sheet will dynamically change to present the relevant stats for that weapon type. The Class field is a text field which allow you to classify the weapon. This is not a required field and can be left blank. <br />&nbsp;<span class=\"melee-img\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; <br />&nbsp;<span class=\"ranged-img\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; <br />For a Melee weapon the range will be set to Engaged, for Ranged weapons select the appropriate range from the dropdown list. The Cost field will convert the input to a currency so all you ned to enter is the number e.g., 15000 and it will reformat as US$15,000.00. <br /><br />The stats on the sheet will be used in rolls when the weapon is \"Active\".</p>\n<br /><br />\n<h2 class=\"headng2\">Armor</h2>\n<p>Setting up different armor types is simple as there are only two main stats to be considered, Armor Rating and Air Supply. <br />&nbsp;<span class=\"armor-img\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; <br />The additional modifiers some armor can have on attributes and abilities can be found on the Modifiers tab. <br />&nbsp;<span class=\"armor-mods\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; <br /><br />The stats and modifiers on the sheet will be used in rolls when the weapon is \"Active\".</p>\n<br /><br />\n<h2 class=\"headng2\">Planet-System</h2>\n<p>The Planet-System sheet provides a method of documenting any planets the party might encounter during their missions. The fields are basic text and are intended to contain summaries. Where more detail is required use the Rich Text editor in the Description tab. Once created these can be dragged on to the Territories sheet as previously mentioned. <br />&nbsp;<span class=\"planet-system-img\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; </p>\n<br /><br />\n<h2 class=\"headng2\">Agenda</h2>\n<p>The Agenda item provides a rich text field which can be used to provide additional scenario based narrative/motivations for the players. These can be used as Agenda or Story cards. Once created they can be dragged on to the PCs sheet where they appear on the Stats tab and can be viewed by the player by clicking on the name.</p>\n<br /><br />\n<h2 class=\"headng2\">Talent</h2>\n<p>This enable you to create talents for your game either homebrew or from the rulebook by adding narrative to the rich test field. When dragged on to a PCs sheet these will appear on the stats tab and can be viewed by the player by clicking on the name. <br /><br /><strong>NOTE:</strong> <br />Talents do not currently have an effect in the system so any impact deriving from a Talent needs to be applied manually during the game. <br />For instance, the Compassion (Medic Talent) allows the PC to push their roll multiple times but the system will by default only allow a roll to be pushed once. In this situation the player should be allowed to re-roll normally and manually increase their Stress.</p>\n<br /><br />\n<h2 class=\"headng2\">Skill-Stunt</h2>\n<p>Skill-stunt items contain a rich text field that can be populated with the Stunt data from the rulebook for each of the skills. <br />If any of the official modules (Starter Set or Core Rules) are installed the text in these items will be ignored but the items should not be deleted, or the system will malfunction.</p>\n<br /><br />\n<h1 class=\"headng\">Rolling Dice</h1>\n<p>Rolls can be pushed for \"Human\" PCs by clicking on the Push icon in the chat window. <br />If the initial roll includes a Facehugger the \"Push\" button will not be displayed. When a roll is pushed the PC's Stress level will automatically be increased by 1. <br />On a Pushed roll the second chat message will show the total successes for both rolls. <br /><br /><strong>NOTE: </strong><em>The PC/Creature token needs to be selected for all rolls.</em> <br /><br />Alien RPG system uses custom dice notation for the Base and Stress dice. <br />If you want to roll ad-hoc dice and don't want to use the macros (See below). You can roll using: <br />/r xdb - for Base dice <br />/r xds - for Stress dice <br />where x is the number of dice. <br />For both just put /r 4db + 2ds</p>\n<br /><br />\n<h1 class=\"headng\">Combat Tracker</h1>\n<p>When rolling for initiative in the combat tracker the combatants will now be sorted in ascending order. <br />&nbsp;<span class=\"initiative-roll\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; <br /><br />By right clicking on an actor in the combat tracker you will see \"Clone Actor\" option appear. This will create a clone of the selected actor to allow the GM to give a Creature multiple initiative rolls. <br /><br />&nbsp;<span class=\"clone-actor\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"roll-clone\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; <br />Additionally, in the chat window an initiative card will be displayed. If you wish to modify these images you can by creating yor own images (250x349px) png files and storing them in the \\images\\cards directory. Name the images in ascending order card-1.png to card-10.png. <br />&nbsp;<span class=\"init-chat-norm\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; <br /><br />If you have purchased either the Starter Set or Core Rules these will automatically be replaced with the official Initiative cards. <br />&nbsp;<span class=\"init-chat-cards\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; <br /><br />There are only 10 initiative cards so if you have a combat with more than 10 actors and roll initiative the system will show a warning and only make rolls for 10 of the actors. <br />You will still be able to roll for the extra actors manually but they will have duplicate initiatives with the existing actors. <br /><br />Alternatively, you can split the party in to two encounters, though I think it's easier to manage with a few duplicates.</p>\n<br /><br />\n<h1 class=\"headng\">Tables</h1>\n<p>When the system is installed it will create the following folder structure:</p>\n<table style=\"width: 43%;\" border=\"0\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 30%;\">Alien Tables -&gt;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 50%;\">Alien Creature Tables&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 30%;\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width: 50%;\">Alien Mother Tables</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>This structure is used by the Creature sheet and two \"roll on table\" macros (See Macros) which are searched to display only the rolltables in those folders. <br />Free League have given me permission to include the Panic Table which can be found in the Alien Mother Tables. <br /><br />If you want to create your own rolltables you should do so in the appropriate folder. <br /><br />When entering the tables from the rulebook for D66 tables use 10*1d6+1d6 as the roll table formula and you will be able to import the ranges as per the book.</p>\n<br /><br />\n<h1 class=\"headng\">System Configuration Options</h1>\n<p>There are a number of system configuration options available to GM and players under Configuration Settings&gt;System Settings: </p>\n<h3 class=\"headng2\">GM Configuration Options</h3>\n<p>&nbsp;<span class=\"gm-settings\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; <br /><br />Hopefully, most of the settings are self explanatory. <br /><br />Enabling the \"Add Settings Button\" will place a quick access button on the Configure Settings sidebar to quickly allow the GM and Players to change fonts and text colours. <br />&nbsp;<span class=\"style-button-settings\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; <br /><br /><br /></p>\n<h3 class=\"headng2\">Player Configuration Options</h3>\n<p>&nbsp;<span class=\"player-settings\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; <br /><br /></p>\n<h3 class=\"headng2\">Font and Colour Configuration Options</h3>\n<p>When I first created the system I wanted to give the feel of the old CRT monitors you see in the films. While this initially looks good after playing for a while the text style and colour can be a little intense. Additionally, having the text colour green can cause issues for people with sight problems. <br /><br />In order to make the system more accessible there are configuration options available to change these settings for individual players. <br />&nbsp;<span class=\"style-settings\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; <br /><br /><br />&nbsp;<span class=\"font-picker-img\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; &nbsp;<span class=\"colour-picker-img\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; <br /><br />Clicking the Reset button will return the system to the defaults.</p>\n<br /><br />\n<h1 class=\"headng\">Macros</h1>\n<p>The Alien system comes with 4 macros that will help you run the game smoothly. <br /><br />These can be found in the Compendium under Macro&gt;Alien. I suggest you right click and do an \"Import All Content\" to get them into your library.</p>\n<ol>\n<li style=\"padding-bottom: 2%;\"><strong style=\"color: deepskyblue;\">Alien - GM Dice Roller:</strong> Allows you to perform ad-hoc dice rolls. Uncheck the GM Only box to make the rolls public.</li>\n<li style=\"padding-bottom: 2%;\"><strong style=\"color: deepskyblue;\">Alien - Player Ad-hoc YZE Dice Roller: </strong>Make this available to your players. They need to have a token selected before running the macro.</li>\n<li style=\"padding-bottom: 2%;\"><strong style=\"color: deepskyblue;\">Alien - Roll on selected Mother table:</strong> provides a drop down listing all the Mother Tables available. Allows multiple rolls against the table and modifiers (+/- x to roll not additional dice).</li>\n<li style=\"padding-bottom: 2%;\"><strong style=\"color: deepskyblue;\">Alien - Roll on selected Creature table: </strong>same as above for Creature tables but no modifiers and all rolls are private to the GM.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>If you want to write your own macros these are the @ tags. <br />For Attributes:</p>\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<li>@str</li>\n<li>@agl</li>\n<li>@wit</li>\n<li>@emp</li>\n<li>@stress</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br />For Skills:</p>\n<ul style=\"list-style-type: none;\">\n<li>@heavyMach</li>\n<li>@closeCbt</li>\n<li>@stamina</li>\n<li>@rangedCbt</li>\n<li>@mobility</li>\n<li>@piloting</li>\n<li>@command</li>\n<li>@manipulation</li>\n<li>@medicalAid</li>\n<li>@observation</li>\n<li>@survival</li>\n<li>@comtech</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br />So to roll for comtech with stress would be: <br />/r (@wit)db + (@comtech)db + (@stress)ds <br /><br /><em>Please note that rolling dice from a macro or in chat will not trigger the \"Push\" or Stress automation.</em></p>\n<br /><br />\n<h1 class=\"headng\">Recommended Add-on Modules</h1>\n<p>While not necessary to use the Alien system of this module I would recommend installing the following Add-on modules as they make the GM's job a lot easier: </p>\n<ul>\n<li style=\"padding-bottom: 2%;\"><strong style=\"color: deepskyblue;\">Dice So Nice:</strong> <br />Alien RPG supports 2 dice face types. <br />There is an issue with DsN where the dice do not pick of the correct colour when first used. Just go into the DsN settings and select Black for the Theme and save. All participants will need to do this.</li>\n<li style=\"padding-bottom: 2%;\"><strong style=\"color: deepskyblue;\">Cursor Hider:</strong> <br />Stops GM and players seeing cursors moving around the screen.</li>\n<li style=\"padding-bottom: 2%;\"><strong style=\"color: deepskyblue;\">PnP - Pointer and Pings:</strong> <br />Useful for pointing things out to the players and pulling their map focus to where you want it.</li>\n<li style=\"padding-bottom: 2%;\"><strong style=\"color: deepskyblue;\">Quick Insert - Search Widget:</strong> <br />Allows you to quickly search for assets and drag them directly on to the scene.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>","_id":"404yGwHqvjb54hUA"}
